1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Hughes was born in 1349, in Sleaford, Lincolnshire, England, his father, Ralph Hughes III, was 49 and his mother, Bernice May Gardner, was 39. He married Lorian de Vernon in 1369, in Sleaford, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1371, at the age of 22."},"et":{"1349–1371":"1349–1371","1349–Female":"1349–Surnud","1370–1392":"1370–1392","1300–1349":"1300–1349","1310–Female":"1310–Surnud","1349":"1349","about 1370":"umbes 1370","1369":"1369","1300":"1300","1310":"1310","1371":"1371","1392":"1392","1370":"1370","Sleaford,,Lincolnshire,England":"Sleaford, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sleaford, Lincolnshire, England":"Sleaford, Lincolnshire, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1349–1371":"1349–1371","1349–Female":"1349–Kuollut","1370–1392":"1370–1392","1300–1349":"1300–1349","1310–Female":"1310–Kuollut","1349":"1349","about 1370":"noin 1370","1369":"1369","1300":"1300","1310":"1310","1371":"1371","1392":"1392","1370":"1370","Sleaford,,Lincolnshire,England":"Sleaford, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sleaford, Lincolnshire, England":"Sleaford, Lincolnshire, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"1349–1371":"1349–1371","1349–Female":"1349–Décédée","1370–1392":"1370–1392","1300–1349":"